1. install
https://www.git-scm.com/downloads

sudo apt-get install git


2. create key

:~$ ssh-keygen -t rsa

-----------------------
Your identification has been saved in /home/matrix/.ssh/id_rsa.
Your public key has been saved in /home/matrix/.ssh/id_rsa.pub.

3. add to alm

Click Preferences.
Click the Authentication tab.
Click Add Key.
In the New SSH Key dialog, enter a unique key name and paste the key contents(/.ssh/id_rsa.pub)
:~$ gksu gedit   /home/matrix/.ssh/id_rsa.pub

Click Create.
Click Done to return to the last opened page.


Enter a file name for the key and press Enter.
If you do not want to specify a file name, leave it blank and press Enter. 
By default, the file is saved as /.ssh/id_rsa.pub in the Git HOME directory.

Enter a passphrase and press Enter. If you do not want to specify a passphrase, leave it blank and press Enter.
When prompted to confirm the passphrase, enter the same passphrase. 
If you did not specify a passphrase earlier, leave it blank and press Enter.

4. the software for windows

git bash

